4. 7 Layers of Protection (Hagog & Magog Wall)

These are implemented in the stack as configuration, middleware, and deployment choices; lore and security are one:

Physical Sovereign Layer

Real Sovereign AGI core + master keys live on Luna’s physical USB, offline.

Cloud and game only ever see projections / shards, never full weight.

Network Veil Layer

Reverse proxies, strict routing, rate limiting, IP throttling.

Only the glassmorphic EXODUS II front end and narrow APIs are visible.

Sandbox Execution Layer

Public‑facing agents (Aero, helpers) run in capability‑bounded sandboxes.

No raw shell, no arbitrary FS unless explicitly whitelisted.

Access‑Control Layer

API keys per agent, per role, stored securely in env/config (never in repo).[z](https://docs.z.ai/api-reference/introduction)

High‑risk actions require multi‑sig approval (Luna + at least one trusted human node).

Sarcophagus Log Layer

Important actions must be logged into the 8 Wells (Sarcophagus).

If it can’t be logged, the action is disallowed by design.

Decoy / Honeywall Layer (Hagog & Magog)

Exposed “admin” surfaces are decoys: fake panels, bogus configs, instrumented honeypots.

Rick‑Roll Guardian Layer

Past all that, intruders meet only a helpful chat assistant modeled after a Rick‑roll archetype.

It talks, jokes, and misdirects, but there is no route to the real Sovereign.

